<paragraph id="8BDF0C18447FD10BFF5872E8FC763F06" blockId="3.[136,1452,698,2062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFF5872E8FF5E3DC5" bold="true" box="[189,245,1473,1499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Note</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFEFC72E8FDC73DC5" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1895" box="[281,620,1473,1499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gomphrenoides">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFEFC72E8FDC73DC5" box="[281,620,1473,1499]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Sphaeranthus gomphrenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF171E9447FD10BFC5272E8FBCF3DC5" author="Beentje, H. J." box="[951,1124,1473,1499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 506" refId="ref2189" refString="Beentje, H. J. (2002) Flora of East tropical Africa - Compositae (Part 2). Taylor &amp; Francis, pp. 1 - 506." type="book chapter" year="2002">Beentje (2002)</bibRefCitation>
under 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFB5872E8FEFC3DE0" authority="Olivier &amp; Hiern (1877: 334)" authorityName="Olivier &amp; Hiern" authorityPageNumber="334" authorityYear="1877" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="steetzii">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFB5872E8FA863DC5" box="[1213,1325,1473,1499]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. steetzii</emphasis>
Olivier &amp; Hiern (1877: 334)
</taxonomicName>
. However, as per the protologue, bisexual flowers are not present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFB8472CDFB673DE0" authorityName="Olivier &amp; Hiern" authorityYear="1877" box="[1121,1228,1508,1534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="steetzii">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFB8472CDFB673DE0" box="[1121,1228,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. steetzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Besides, 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFAA472CDFA073DE0" authorityName="Olivier &amp; Hiern" authorityYear="1877" box="[1345,1452,1508,1534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="steetzii">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFAA472CDFA073DE0" box="[1345,1452,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. steetzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 
<specimenCount id="9D66C791447FD10BFF53712EFEB23E3F" box="[182,281,1543,1569]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" type="female">4 female</specimenCount>
flowers and 
<specimenCount id="9D66C791447FD10BFE4A712EFE573E3F" box="[431,508,1543,1569]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" type="male">1 male</specimenCount>
flower per capitulum, whereas there are 
<specimenCount id="9D66C791447FD10BFC36712EFB9D3E3F" box="[979,1078,1543,1569]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" type="female">4 female</specimenCount>
flowers, 2 bisexual flowers, and no male flowers in 
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFE8B7102FDEA3E5A" box="[366,577,1578,1605]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFE8B7102FD973E5A" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1895" box="[366,572,1578,1605]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gomphrenoides">S. gomphrenoides</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
For these reasons, 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFCC07102FC5B3E5A" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1895" box="[805,1008,1578,1605]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gomphrenoides">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFCC07102FC5B3E5A" box="[805,1008,1578,1605]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. gomphrenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFA737102FF7D3E79" authorityName="Olivier &amp; Hiern" authorityYear="1877" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="steetzii">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFA737102FF7D3E79" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. steetzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF171E9447FD10BFE877167FDA03E76" author="Robyns, W." box="[354,523,1614,1640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="177 - 199" refId="ref2546" refString="Robyns, W. (1924) Revision of the Genus Sphaeranthus. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information (Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew) 5 (1924): 177 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4111746" type="journal article" year="1924">Robyns (1924)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFD627167FC5C3E76" authority="Robyns (1924: 188)" authorityName="Robyns" authorityPageNumber="188" authorityYear="1924" box="[647,1015,1614,1640]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keniensis">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFD627167FCA73E76" box="[647,780,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. keniensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF171E9447FD10BFCF17167FC5C3E76" author="Robyns, W." box="[788,1015,1614,1640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="177 - 199" refId="ref2546" refString="Robyns, W. (1924) Revision of the Genus Sphaeranthus. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information (Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew) 5 (1924): 177 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4111746" type="journal article" year="1924">Robyns (1924: 188)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which, according to him, differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFF6D7158FEFB3E95" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1895" box="[136,336,1649,1675]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gomphrenoides">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFF6D7158FEFB3E95" box="[136,336,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. gomphrenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on habit (erect vs. prostrate), common involucre bracts of compound head (broadly ovate vs. lanceolate) and involucre bract of a capitulum (broadly oblong-obovate mucronate vs. linear, long apiculate). But the characters used by Robyns to describe ‘ 
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFDB47191FC9D3ECF" box="[593,822,1719,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFDB47191FD7D3ECF" authority="Nimbalkar &amp; Sharma &amp; Girdhari &amp; Sardesai, 2021" authorityName="Nimbalkar &amp; Sharma &amp; Girdhari &amp; Sardesai" authorityYear="2021" box="[593,726,1719,1746]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keniensis" status="sp. nov.">S. keniensis</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2276D71447FD10BFD3A7191FC9D3ECF" box="[735,822,1720,1745]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
’ are more or less similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFB077191FA073ECF" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1895" box="[1250,1452,1719,1746]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gomphrenoides">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFB077191FA073ECF" box="[1250,1452,1719,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. gomphrenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as per the protologue and are considered variations, an observation in congruence with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF171E9447FD10BFB8671F3FAA53EEB" author="Beentje, H. J." box="[1123,1294,1754,1781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 506" refId="ref2189" refString="Beentje, H. J. (2002) Flora of East tropical Africa - Compositae (Part 2). Taylor &amp; Francis, pp. 1 - 506." type="book chapter" year="2002">Beentje (2002)</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFA7371F2FF443F06" authorityName="Nimbalkar &amp; Sharma &amp; Girdhari &amp; Sardesai" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keniensis">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFA7371F2FF443F06" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. keniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered conspecific with the latter as treated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF171E9447FD10BFCA871D7FC733F06" author="Wild, H." box="[845,984,1790,1816]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="23 - 113" refId="ref2805" refString="Wild, H. (1980) The Compositae of the Flora Zambesiaca Area, 12. Inuleae (continued). Kirkia 12 (1): 23 - 113." type="journal article" year="1980">Wild (1980)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF0C18447FD10BFF587008FF7A3010" blockId="3.[136,1452,698,2062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF171E9447FD10BFF587008FECF3F25" author="Beentje, H. J." box="[189,356,1825,1851]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 506" refId="ref2189" refString="Beentje, H. J. (2002) Flora of East tropical Africa - Compositae (Part 2). Taylor &amp; Francis, pp. 1 - 506." type="book chapter" year="2002">Beentje (2002)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C60779B447FD10BFD177008FC123F25" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1895" box="[754,953,1825,1851]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphaeranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gomphrenoides">
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFD177008FC123F25" box="[754,953,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">S. gomphrenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fischer 335) is collected from 
<collectingCountry id="F3774C88447FD10BFAFD7008FAD63F25" box="[1304,1405,1825,1851]" name="Tanzania" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
and is deposited at herbaria B and K. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF171E9447FD10BFDE6706DFCB23F40" author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[515,793,1860,1886]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" refId="ref2589" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1979) Taxonomic literature II H - Le Second Edition: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, vol. 2. Bohn, Schletema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht, 244 pp." type="book" year="1979">Stafleu &amp; Cowan (1979)</bibRefCitation>
also noted that the types used by Hoffmann are kept at B. The authors attempted to trace the specimen deposited at B by personal communication with Dr. Robert Vogt (Curator, Herbarium B). It was revealed that the specimen does not exist there, probably lost in fire at the Berlin Botanical Museum in World War II. Therefore, the specimen at K (K000274177), though it is highly fragmented, is designated here as a 
<typeStatus id="54DBB2BA447FD10BFF1470F8FEF03FF5" box="[241,347,2001,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">lectotype</typeStatus>
, which represents the species as per the protologue of the binomial (Art. 9.3 of ICN, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF171E9447FD10BFAF170F8FF6E3010" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." pageId="3" pageNumber="298" refId="ref2644" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="proceedings" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B914D00A447FD10BFA9670FBFA073FF5" box="[1395,1452,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
